> These wontons are the perfect combination of spicy and sweet: jalapeño peppers and cream cheese filling are wrapped in a deliciously crispy wonton wrapper. They're gooey on the inside and crunchy on the outside. And what could be better than gyoza (Japanese-style dumplings) from SUMM?! Why, serving them alongside crispy golden vegetable spring rolls, of course! Filled with minced pork, cabbage, scallions, shiitake mushrooms, and ginger, these dumplings pair perfectly with cabbage, carrot, and mushroom-packed spring rolls. This threesome makes the perfect meal, app, or anytime snack! No matter how you heat them up, these gems are best served with SUMM! (Sauces included!)

== Jalapeño Popper Wontons ==

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 400 degrees. Line a #baking sheet{} with #parchment paper{}.

Remove @Crispy Jalapeno Popper Wontons{1} from packaging; place on a prepared #sheet{} about ½ inch apart.

Bake until cooked through, ~{6-8%minutes}. Let cool for ~{2-3%minutes} and serve with @chili sauce{} on the side.

== Alternative Air Fryer Method ==

Arrange wontons ½ inch apart in an #air fryer basket{} (you may have to work in batches). Air-fry at 325 degrees until cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Let cool for ~{2-3%minutes} and serve with @chili sauce{} on the side.

> Air fryer times may vary.

== Dumplings ==

Heat @cooking oil{1%tbsp} in a large #pan{} over high heat. Add @Pork & Shiitake Gyoza Dumplings{1}, flat sides down, and @water{1/3%cup} (be careful of splatter!); cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium and cook until water evaporates and bottoms are crispy, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Serve with @gyoza sauce{} on the side for dipping.

> Recipe suggestion: Find instructions for alternate cooking methods on the package!

== Spring Rolls - Oven ==

Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

Place @Vegetable Spring Rolls{1} on a baking sheet in a single layer; bake, turning halfway through, until crispy, ~{18%minutes}. Remove from oven; let cool for ~{2%minutes}.

Serve with @plum sauce{}.

== Spring Rolls - Air Fryer ==

Preheat #air fryer{} to 390 degrees.

Place spring rolls in #air fryer basket{} in a single layer; heat, tossing halfway through, until crispy, ~{8-10%minutes}. Remove from air fryer; let cool for ~{2%minutes}.

Serve with @plum sauce{}.

> Keep refrigerated until ready to heat; best if used within 7 days.